2 (3) As used in [sections 1 and 2], the following definitions apply:
3 (a) "Electronic consumer product" includes electronic devices as defined in 45-6-310 as well as
4 motor vehicles as defined in 61-1-101.
5 (b)(a) "Entity" means a company that manufactures or distributes an electronic consumer product
6 personally owned property or that provides service for an electronic consumer product's its functionality.
7 (c)(b) “Hard reset” means the restoration of an electronic consumer product personally owned
8 property to the state the electronic consumer product it was in when it left the factory. Other terms commonly
9 used are "factory reset" and "master reset".
10 (d)(c) "Individual" means a natural person.
11 (e)(d) "Kill switch" means a mechanism that may be engaged remotely, regardless of the owner's
12 consent, and is used to:
13 (i) shut down or perform a hard reset on an electronic consumer product personally owned
14 property;
15 (ii) hasten the battery drainage of an electronic consumer product personally owned property; or
16 (iii) shorten the software lifespan of an electronic consumer product personally owned property.
17
18 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Enforcement -- damages. (1) A violation of [section 1] is a violation of
19 30-14-103.
20 (2) The department of justice may bring an action to restrain any unlawful act pursuant to the
21 provisions of Title 30, chapter 14, part 1.
22 (3) An individual whose electronic consumer product personally owned property has a kill switch
23 activated in violation of [section 1] may bring an action pursuant to 30-14-133, except that:
24 (a) the individual needs to show only a violation of [section 1] for that individual’s electronic
25 consumer product personally owned property and is not required to show any other ascertainable loss of
26 money or property; and
